The paper discusses autoencoders, which are commonly used in machine learning and fall under the category of deep learning. The focus of the paper is on improving the ability of autoencoders to interpolate, which is a task related to image processing and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed regularization procedure involves training a critic network, which is a technique commonly used in generative adversarial networks (GANs) and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the learned representations on downstream tasks, which is a topic related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, which covers topics related to machine learning and deep learning.
